{"lemma":"صَبِيٌّ","slug":"صَبِيٌّ","root":"ص.ب.#","root_slug":"ص-ب-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ب-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَبِيّ","root":"صبو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23746"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rejuvenate, to make youthful again","tags":["transitive"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23746","headword_ar":"صَبِىٌّ","root":"Sbw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A youth, boy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male child;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulaAmN","text_ar":"غُلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a young male child;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before he is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulaAm","text_ar":"غُلَام"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that has not yet been weaned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) so called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the time of his birth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAbK","text_ar":"صَابٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabiY~N","text_ar":"صَبِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; these two words being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAdirN","text_ar":"قَادِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadiyrN","text_ar":"قَدِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the pl. of the former is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiboyapN","text_ar":"صِبْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc., in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the kesreh before it, like as is said in the M respecting another of the pls.,] (S, M, Msb, K, but not in the CK,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibowapN","text_ar":"صِبْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA, in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabowapN","text_ar":"صَبْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuboyapN","text_ar":"صُبْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaboyapN","text_ar":"صَبْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA, but not in the CK,) [or rather the last two are quasi-pl. ns.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobK","text_ar":"اَصْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[another pl. of pauc.] (K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobiyapN","text_ar":"اَصْبِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[also a pl. of pauc.], (M, K,) but this last is said by J to have been unused, because the usage of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiboyapN","text_ar":"صِبْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"rendered it needless, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiboyaAnN","text_ar":"صِبْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K, but not in the CK,) in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the kesreh before it, (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuboyaAnN","text_ar":"صُبْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) as some say, preserving the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"notwithstanding the dammeh, (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SibowaAnN","text_ar":"صِبْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, but not in the CK,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SubowaAnN","text_ar":"صُبْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) and [ISd says,] accord. to Sb, the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiboyapN","text_ar":"صِبْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSayobiyapN","text_ar":"اُصَيْبِيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobiyapN","text_ar":"اَصْبِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subay~apN","text_ar":"صُبَيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", each irreg.; but in my opinion,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Subay~apN","text_ar":"صُبَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiboyapN","text_ar":"صِبْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSayobiyapN","text_ar":"اُصَيْبِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobiyapN","text_ar":"اَصْبِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) [J says,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSayobiyapN","text_ar":"اُصَيْبِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in poetry as being the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobiyapN","text_ar":"اَصْبِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sabiy~apN","text_ar":"صَبِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A young woman, girl,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female child;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) and so too, [sometimes,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabiY~N","text_ar":"صَبِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaAyaA","text_ar":"صَبَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u AlS~iboyaAni","text_ar":"اُمُّ الصِّبْيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a term applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The flatus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flatulence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iyHu","text_ar":"الرِّيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is incident to children."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Am","text_ar":"ام"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [Golius, in that art., explains it as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Larva, terriculamentum puerorum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"on the authority of Meyd.: and also as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Epilepsy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"on the authority of Ibn-Beytár.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabiY~N","text_ar":"صَبِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pupil of the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) but Kr ascribes this meaning to the vulgar. (M.) ―         -b4-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity of each of the jaw-bones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) i. e. (TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~abiy~aAni","text_ar":"الصَّبِيَّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two extremities of the two jaw-bones"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, TA) of the camel and of other animals: or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two edges curving outwards from the middle of the two jaw-bones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or, accord. to the A,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thin portions of the two extremities thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is [said to be] tropical. (TA.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bone below the lobe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lobule, of each of the two ears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head of the bone that is below the lobe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lobule, of each of the two ears by the space of about three fingers put together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b5-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edge"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~","text_ar":"حَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":") of the sword: (M, K, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ridge"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof, (M, TA, in the copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awo gayorihi","text_ar":"اَوْ غَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awo Eayoruhu","text_ar":"اَوْ عَيْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which rises in"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"along"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its middle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA;) and likewise of a spear-head: (M, TA:) or, accord. to the A, that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a sword"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"below,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exclusive of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwna","text_ar":"دُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zubap","text_ar":"ظُبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the human foot; (M, A, TA; in the copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osu Alqawomi","text_ar":"رَاْسُ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osu Alqadami","text_ar":"رَاْسُ القَدَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; TA;) i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thereof]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimaArap","text_ar":"حِمَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the toes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~abiy~aAni","text_ar":"الصَّبِيَّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two sides of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel's saddle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b7-  It is also said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiboyaAnu Aljaliydi","text_ar":"صِبْيَانُ الجَلِيدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The grains of hoar-frost that resemble pearls:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiboyaAnu AlmaTari","text_ar":"صِبْيَانُ المَطَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the small drops of rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but accord. to the author of the “ Khasáïl, ” it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Siy^obaAn","text_ar":"صِيْبَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suw^aAbapN","text_ar":"صُوَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.], with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"and then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","M","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B5%D8%A8%D9%8A/","headword_ar":"صبي","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_12","lexicon_en":"Al-Muṭarrizī, al-Mughrib fī Tartīb al-Muʿrib (d. 1213 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المغرب في ترتيب المعرب للمُطَرِّزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22082#645778","body_html":"(ص ب ي) : (الصَّبِيُّ) الصَّغِيرُ قَبْلَ الْغُلَامِ وَجَمْعُهُ صِبْيَةٌ وَصِبْيَانٌ (وَبِتَصْغِيرِهِ) مُرَخَّمًا سُمِّيَ صُبَيُّ بْنُ مَعْبَدٍ التَّغْلِبِيُّ أَسْلَمَ وَلَقِيَ زَيْدَ بْنَ صُوحَانَ."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_51","lexicon_en":"Habib Anthony Salmone, An Advanced Learner's Arabic-English Dictionary (1889)","lexicon_ar":"حبيب سالمون، قاموس عربي انجليزي متقدم للمتعلمين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22082#209fac","body_html":"صبي<br> صَبَى(n. ac. صَبَاْي)<br>a. see supra <br> (a)<br> صَاْبَيَa. Inclined (spear); put back, sheathed (<br> sword ). <br> أَصْبَيَa. Captivated, fascinated.<br> <br> تَصَبَّيَa. Deceived, beguiled; seduced.<br> <br> تَصَاْبَيَإِسْتَصْبَيَa. see I (a)<br> صَبْوَة []<br>a. Boyishness; youthful folly.<br> <br> صَبًا (pl.<br> أَصْبَآء [] <br> صَبَوَات )<br>a. East wind.<br> b. Breeze; zephyr. <br> صِبًاa. Inclination, liking.<br> b. Amorous dalliance.<br> <br> صَابِيَة []<br>a. North-east wind.<br> <br> صَبِيّ [] (pl.<br> صِبْيَة [] <br> أَصْبِيَة [] صُِبْيَان [صِبْيَاْن صَبڤيَ])<br>a. Boy; youth, lad.<br> <br> صَبِيَّة [] (pl.<br> صَبَايَا)<br>a. Girl; maiden; lass."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_17","lexicon_en":"Al-Fayyūmī, Al-Miṣbāḥ al-Munīr fī Gharīb al-Sharḥ al-Kabīr (d. 1368 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المصباح المنير للفيّومي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22082#798d3f","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">ص ب ي</span><span> : الصَّبِيُّ الصَّغِيرُ وَالْجَمْعُ صِبْيَةٌ بِالْكَسْرِ وَصِبْيَانٌ وَالصِّبَا بِالْكَسْرِ مَقْصُورٌ الصِّغَرُ وَالصَّبَاءُ وِزَانُ كَلَامٍ لُغَةٌ فِيهِ يُقَالُ كَانَ ذَلِكَ فِي صِبَاهُ وَفِي صَبَائِهِ وَالصَّبَا وِزَانُ الْعَصَا الرِّيحُ تَهُبُّ مِنْ مَطْلَعِ الشَّمْسِ وَصَبَا صُبُوًّا مِنْ بَابِ قَعَدَ وَصَبْوَةً أَيْضًا مِثْلُ شَهْوَةِ مَالٍ وَصَبَأَ مِنْ دِينٍ إلَى دِينٍ يَصْبَأُ مَهْمُوزٌ بِفَتْحَتَيْنِ خَرَجَ فَهُوَ صَابِئٌ ثُمَّ جُعِلَ هَذَا اللَّقَبُ عَلَمًا عَلَى طَائِفَةٍ مِنْ الْكُفَّارِ يُقَالُ إنَّهَا تَعْبُدُ الْكَوَاكِبَ فِي الْبَاطِنِ وَتُنْسَبُ إلَى النَّصْرَانِيَّةِ فِي الظَّاهِرِ وَهُمْ الصَّابِئَةُ وَالصَّابِئُونَ وَيَدَّعُونَ أَنَّهُمْ عَلَى دِينِ</span><br><span>صَابِئِ بْنِ شِيثِ بْنِ آدَمَ وَيَجُوزُ التَّخْفِيفُ فَيُقَالُ الصَّابُونُ وَقَرَأَ بِهِ نَافِعٌ. </span>"}]}}